  <description type="morphology">Stems terete, finely sulcate, highly branched, bark tan becoming gray, twigs mostly green, minutely ridged, papillate-scabrous. Leaves ascending to spreading, sulcate adaxially, 5–20 × 0.5–1 mm; axillary fascicles sometimes present. Phyllaries 3–6 × 0.8–1.5 mm, mostly chartaceous, midveins enlarged distally, evident as green to brown patches, apices acute. Disc corollas 5–6 mm, tubes glabrous or puberulent, lobes 1–2.5 mm; style branches 2–2.5 mm, appendages 1.2–1.5 mm. Cypselae 3–4 mm, hairy; pappi 4–6 mm. 2n = 18.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering late summer–fall (or with adequate rain).</description>
  <description type="habitat">Often in gypseous, calcareous, saline, or gravelly soils;</description>
  <description type="elevation">700–1500 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Tex.; Mexico (Chihuahua, Coahuila, Durango, Nuevo León).</description>
